	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It wasn't &quot;polluted&quot; with shovelware. All the major platforms have shovelware, and I'd actually say Wii U has less of it than other places. It has less of <em>everything</em> though. Most developers knew it was a bust to release there and avoided it. (PS4 and XB1 publishing policies are both more indie-friendly than Wii U's IMO.)<br /><br />You don't notice the shovelware so much on PS4 because there's a variety of <em>good</em> stuff to look at in the store instead. On Wii U there's hardly anything at all on the store, you can't look at a &quot;best of&quot; selection because there isn't enough to make such a thing. It's like, 1st party, then maybe minecraft and shovel knight. It was so spare that <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meme_Run" class="postlink">Meme Run</a> ended up on the console's main menu for a month or two because it was the only thing selling on eShop at the time!

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


